# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# .NET build output for the C# test fixtures (dev-only dependency, see
# tests/fixtures/csharp/README.md) — never a runtime dependency of vmnet
tests/fixtures/csharp/bin/
tests/fixtures/csharp/obj/

# .NET build output for the separate P/Invoke checker fixture (Fase
# 3.69) — see tests/fixtures/csharp-pinvoke/PInvokeFixture.cs's own doc
# comment for why it's a distinct project from tests/fixtures/csharp.
tests/fixtures/csharp-pinvoke/bin/
tests/fixtures/csharp-pinvoke/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/jint-demo wrapper (JintWrapper.cs is
# committed source; the compiled JintWrapper.dll it produces is not — see
# examples/jint-demo/README.md)
examples/jint-demo/bin/
examples/jint-demo/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/closedxml-demo wrapper (same
# rationale as jint-demo above — GraphicEngineWrapper.cs is committed
# source, the compiled GraphicEngineWrapper.dll it produces is not)
examples/closedxml-demo/bin/
examples/closedxml-demo/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/calculator classlib + optional
# CoreCLR-comparison project (same rationale — Calculator.cs and
# coreclr/Program.cs are committed source, the DLLs/exes they produce
# are not)
examples/calculator/bin/
examples/calculator/obj/
examples/calculator/coreclr/bin/
examples/calculator/coreclr/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/dapper-demo wrapper (same rationale
# as jint-demo above — DapperDemoWrapper.cs is committed source, the
# compiled DapperDemoWrapper.dll it produces is not)
examples/dapper-demo/bin/
examples/dapper-demo/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/sqlite-demo wrapper (same rationale
# as jint-demo above — SqliteDemoWrapper.cs is committed source, the
# compiled SqliteDemoWrapper.dll it produces is not), plus the real
# SQLite file main.go writes fresh on every run (a build artifact, same
# posture as openxml-demo's own report.docx below — not committed test
# data, unlike the *.xls/*.xlsx fixtures other demos ship as real input).
examples/sqlite-demo/bin/
examples/sqlite-demo/obj/
examples/sqlite-demo/*.db

# .NET build output for the examples/di-demo wrapper (same rationale as
# jint-demo above — DiDemoWrapper.cs is committed source, the compiled
# DiDemoWrapper.dll it produces is not)
examples/di-demo/bin/
examples/di-demo/obj/

# .NET build output for the examples/fluentvalidation-demo wrapper (same
# rationale as jint-demo above — FvDemoWrapper.cs is committed source,
# the compiled FvDemoWrapper.dll it produces is not)
examples/fluentvalidation-demo/bin/
examples/fluentvalidation-demo/obj/

# same rationale — Bench.cs is committed source, its compiled Bench.dll
# and .vmnet/ package cache are build artifacts.
benchmarks/bin/
benchmarks/obj/
benchmarks/.vmnet/

# macOS Finder metadata
.DS_Store

# examples/openxml-demo's own generated output (main.go writes this fresh
# on every run — a build artifact, not a fixture, unlike the *.xls/*.xlsx
# testdata other demos commit as their real read-side input)
examples/openxml-demo/report.docx

# vmnet's own NuGet package cache (`vmnet add`/`restore`, see
# docs/ROADMAP.md Fase 3) — downloaded .nupkg files, never committed.
# vmnet.json/vmnet.lock.json are NOT ignored here: a real project commits
# them for reproducible restores, same as go.sum/package-lock.json.
.vmnet/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/
